ú Choille</i>’, a personal name meaning ‘hound of the wood’, which has also been mistranslated   Cox  , as if formed with <i>coileach</i> ‘cock, rooster’."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":35,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas Wood SR was born in 1420, in Childrey, Berkshire, England. He had at least 1 son."},"et":{"1420–":"1420–Surnud","1446–1502":"1446–1502","1420–Male":"1420–Surnud","1502":"1502","1446":"1446","1455":"1455","1420":"1420","Childrey, Berkshire, England":"Childrey, Berkshire, England"},"fi":{"1420–":"1420–Kuollut","1446–1502":"1446–1502","1420–Male":"1420–Kuollut","1502":"1502","1446":"1446","1455":"1455","1420":"1420","Childrey, Berkshire, England":"Childrey, Berkshire, England"},"fr":{"1420–":"1420–Décédé","1446–1502":"1446–1502","1420–Male":"1420–Décédé","1502":"1502","1446":"1446","1455":"1455","1420":"1420","Childrey, Berkshire, England":"Childrey, Berkshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Thomas Wood SR est né en 1420, à Childrey, 